<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1266,1795]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">
This species was known from 
<collectingCountry box="[570,615,1411,1434]" name="Iran" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">Iran</collectingCountry>
and Central Asia (
<bibRefCitation author="Cate" box="[849,1049,1411,1435]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Cate, P. C., Sanchez-Ruiz, A., Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (2007) Elateridae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 4. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 89 - 209." type="book" year="2007">
Cate 
<emphasis box="[915,978,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
) and already was reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,288,1446,1471]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobson" box="[308,489,1446,1471]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Jacobson, G. G. (1913) Zhuki Rossii i Zapadnoy Evropy. Rukovodstvo k opredeleniyu zhukov [Beetles of Russia and Western Europe. Manual for identification of beetles]. Fasc. 10. St. - Petersburg: A. F. Devrien. pp. 721 - 864. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1913">Jacobson, 1913</bibRefCitation>
) but without any exact data. This is the first reliable record of 
<taxonomicName box="[1263,1391,1446,1470]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis box="[1263,1391,1446,1470]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<collectingCountry box="[151,292,1482,1507]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1266,1795]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,445,1518,1543]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">Systematic remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[454,578,1518,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis box="[454,578,1518,1542]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rather distinctive species of the genus. Externally it is similar to such western Palaearctic species as 
<taxonomicName authority="Platia &amp; Schimmel, 1994" authorityName="Platia &amp; Schimmel" authorityYear="1994" box="[492,892,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapleri">
<emphasis box="[492,600,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. kapleri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Platia" box="[607,892,1554,1579]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Platia, G. &amp; Schimmel, R. (1994) Descrizione di tre nuove specie di elateridi di Grecia, Turchia e Siria, con note su Agriotes cribrithorax Pic, 1910 (Coleoptera, Elateridae). Lavori - Societa Veneziana di Scienze Naturali, 19, 77 - 82." type="journal article" year="1994">Platia &amp; Schimmel, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the shape of its genitalia is notably different (
<figureCitation box="[159,285,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 50" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1254,1277]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,407,1215]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1435,385,1233]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 50. Lacon funebris, from Afghanistan (Figs. 47 – 49) and Tajikistan (Fig. 50). 47. Habitus, dorsal view, female (16 mm). 48. Ovipositor, ventral view. 49. Part of female genital tract, general view. 50. Aedeagus, ventral view. Not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263293/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">Fig. 48–50</figureCitation>
; see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Platia" box="[394,677,1590,1615]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Platia, G. &amp; Schimmel, R. (1994) Descrizione di tre nuove specie di elateridi di Grecia, Turchia e Siria, con note su Agriotes cribrithorax Pic, 1910 (Coleoptera, Elateridae). Lavori - Societa Veneziana di Scienze Naturali, 19, 77 - 82." type="journal article" year="1994">Platia &amp; Schimmel 1994</bibRefCitation>
). On the other hand, the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1221,1590,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis box="[1099,1221,1590,1614]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Candeze, 1874" authorityName="Candeze" authorityYear="1874" box="[248,567,1626,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[248,373,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. unicolor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Candeze" box="[389,558,1626,1651]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Candeze, E. (1874) Revision de la Monographie des Elaterides. 1 fascicule. Memoires de la Societe Royale des Science de Liege, 2 (4), I - VIII, 1 - 218. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 47120" type="journal article" year="1874">Candèze, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[622,723,1627,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nadaii">
<emphasis box="[622,723,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. nadaii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the general appearance and female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[1314,1436,1627,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis box="[1314,1436,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are quite different (
<figureCitation box="[365,447,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 50" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1254,1277]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,407,1215]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1435,385,1233]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 50. Lacon funebris, from Afghanistan (Figs. 47 – 49) and Tajikistan (Fig. 50). 47. Habitus, dorsal view, female (16 mm). 48. Ovipositor, ventral view. 49. Part of female genital tract, general view. 50. Aedeagus, ventral view. Not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263293/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
; see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Platia" box="[552,811,1662,1687]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Platia, G. &amp; Gudenzi, I. (1999) New species and new or interesting records of click-beetles from Iran and Iraq (Coleoptera, Elateridae). Entomologica Fennica, 10, 117 - 125." type="journal article" year="1999">Platia &amp; Gudenzi 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Platia" box="[822,1076,1662,1687]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Platia, G. &amp; Nemeth, T. (2011) On some Palaearctic click beetles in the Hungarian Natural History Museum (Coleoptera: Elateridae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 103, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="2011">Platia &amp; Németh 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Two other species similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schwarz, 1900" authorityName="Schwarz" authorityYear="1900" box="[257,562,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="griseus">
<emphasis box="[257,369,1699,1722]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. griseus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schwarz" box="[384,554,1698,1723]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Schwarz, O. (1900) Neue palaarktische Elateriden. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 44 (1), 98 - 111." type="journal article" year="1900">Schwarz, 1900</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kraatz, 1882" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1882" box="[618,938,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incomptus">
<emphasis box="[618,764,1699,1722]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. incomptus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kraatz" box="[779,930,1699,1723]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Heyden, L. von &amp; Kraatz, G. (1882) Kafer um Samarkand, gesammelt von Haberhauer. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 26 (2), 297 - 338." type="journal article" year="1882">Kraatz, 1882</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, were described from Central Asia (
<bibRefCitation author="Heyden" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Heyden, L. von &amp; Kraatz, G. (1882) Kafer um Samarkand, gesammelt von Haberhauer. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 26 (2), 297 - 338." type="journal article" year="1882">Heyden &amp; Kraatz 1882</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwarz" box="[342,509,1734,1759]" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" refString="Schwarz, O. (1900) Neue palaarktische Elateriden. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 44 (1), 98 - 111." type="journal article" year="1900">Schwarz 1900</bibRefCitation>
). These species, judging by the original descriptions, seem closely related to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Lacon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="293">L. funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and probably are no more than morphological forms of this variable species.
</paragraph>
